cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.LO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing determinants and adjoints of matrices over abstract rings, which involves symbolic manipulation. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms and their implementation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a new algorithm for computing matrix adjoints. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with the computation of minimum polynomials of linearly generated sequences. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves the deduction of an algorithm by applying program differentiation techniques.
